Parliament&#8217;s Communications Committee has recommended that former Busa CEO Khanyisile Kweyama chair SABC&#8217;s interim board. PARLIAMENT - Parliament s Communications Committee has recommended that former Business Unity South Africa (Busa) CEO Khanyisile Kweyama chair the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) s interim board.The committee adopted its report nominating five members for the interim board on Tuesday.They are Krish Naidoo, Febe Potgieter-Gqubule, Mathatha Tsedu and John Matisonn.#SABC Parly communications cttee recommends former BUSA CEO Khanyisa Kweyama as chair and Mathatha TSedu as deputy chair of interim board GDParliament s communications committee wants Kweyama to chair the SABC s interim board, with veteran journalist and former editor Tsedu as her deputy.The committee s report recommending the members of the interim board is set to come before the National Assembly on Wednesday. Once approved, it will be forwarded to President Jacob Zuma, who makes the appointments.Communications Minister Faith Muthambi has decided to take on review the report of Parliament s inquiry into the SABC board. It s unclear what impact this will have on the interim board s appointment.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)